{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing mandatory information element in RRC connection type handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrcType` function in the AS simulator was not properly handling a default/unknown connection type, causing incorrect logging and potential issues in signaling message processing. When the RRC connection type was set to 0x00 (indicating an unknown or default type), the function would fall through to the generic \"Unknown\" case instead of explicitly handling this valid state.\n\nThis manifested as misleading log messages during NAS signaling procedures where the connection type wasn't explicitly set. The issue was particularly noticeable during emergency call scenarios where the connection type might not be fully determined.\n\nThe fix adds explicit handling for the unknown connection type by:\n1. Defining `NET_ESTABLISH_TYPE_UNKNOWN` with value 0x00\n2. Adding the corresponding `AS_TYPE_UNKNOWN` enum value\n3. Updating the `rrcType` function to return \"UNKNOWN\" for this case\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/networkDef.h`: Added `NET_ESTABLISH_TYPE_UNKNOWN` constant\n- `openair2/COMMON/as_message.h`: Added `AS_TYPE_UNKNOWN` enum value\n- `openair3/NAS/TEST/AS_SIMULATOR/as_data.c`: Updated `rrcType` function to handle unknown type explicitly\n"
}